Wash and dry produce. Finely dice @tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@red onion{1}; finely chop a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Zest and
quarter @lime{1}. Halve, deseed, and finely chop @jalapeño{1}. Peel and finely
chop @garlic{1%clove}.

> Leave seeds in jalapeño for more spice!

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to
serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, chopped onion, half the
lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, and as
much jalapeño as you like. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
sliced onion and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add ground turkey, garlic, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and another
big pinch of salt. TIP: If you like things spicy, add any remaining jalapeño.

Using a #spatula{}, arrange turkey into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until
browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up into pieces; cook, stirring
occasionally, until turkey is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. TIP: If there's
excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

To pan with turkey, stir in @tomato paste{1} and @beef stock concentrate{1},
then add 1/4 cup water. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted; turn off heat.

While turkey cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}
with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Add water
1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining lime zest and @butter{1%tablespoon}.
Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with turkey mixture, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup},
salsa, and crema. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining
lime wedges on the side.